WHAT THE HELL?
HE'S CONTESTING IT?

13:26.400 --> 13:29.065
YEAH, PROBABLY.

13:29.067 --> 13:31.132
Well, I guess there's nothing
you can do about that.

13:31.134 --> 13:35.465
NOPE. EXCEPT FIND A DRUG ADDICT
TO KILL HIM.

13:35.467 --> 13:37.998
-MARCIE.
-Maybe Eddie.

13:38.000 --> 13:39.865
DON'T SAY THINGS
LIKE THAT.

13:39.867 --> 13:41.199
WHY NOT?

13:41.201 --> 13:44.165
BECAUSE THEN YOU'LL END UP
IN KELLY'S SHOES.

13:44.167 --> 13:45.898
YEAH, YEAH, I KNOW.

13:45.900 --> 13:48.265
YOU SHOULD JUST TRY
AND LET IT GO.

13:48.267 --> 13:50.398
YEAH, I'M TRYING.
HE'S NOT.

13:50.400 --> 13:51.732
I KNOW.

13:51.734 --> 13:54.965
I WISH I COULD JUST
MOVE AWAY TO ANOTHER TOWN.

13:54.967 --> 13:57.365
YEAH, THAT WOULD BE NICE,
WOULDN'T IT?

13:57.367 --> 13:58.565
BUT MY KIDS ARE HERE.

13:58.567 --> 14:00.099
YEAH, I KNOW.

14:00.101 --> 14:01.498
And I just wouldn't
want to leave them.

14:01.500 --> 14:04.065
YOU KNOW, EVEN THOUGH IT'S OVER
BETWEEN ME AND ALEX.

14:04.067 --> 14:07.032
I KNOW.
I KNOW YOU DON'T, BABE.

14:07.034 --> 14:10.165
SO, UH, WHAT TIME
WILL YOU BE DONE?

14:10.167 --> 14:13.932
I'LL BE HOME AT 7:00
FOR DINNER.

14:13.934 --> 14:15.532
OKAY.

14:15.534 --> 14:17.832
FANCY GOING OUT
TO DINNER TONIGHT?

14:17.834 --> 14:19.465
I'D LIKE THAT, YEAH.

14:19.467 --> 14:22.065
I'LL SEE YOU
WHEN YOU GET HOME.

14:22.067 --> 14:23.665
OKAY.

14:23.667 --> 14:24.865
BYE.

14:24.867 --> 14:26.965
Bye.

14:26.967 --> 14:28.698
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

14:28.700 --> 14:36.465
♪♪

14:36.467 --> 14:44.198
♪♪

14:44.200 --> 14:51.932
♪♪

14:51.934 --> 14:54.065
-HI.
-HEY.

14:54.067 --> 14:56.665
-[ CHUCKLES ]
-YOU SLEPT A LONG TIME.

14:56.667 --> 15:00.532
-YEAH?
-HOW DO YOU FEEL?

15:00.534 --> 15:02.331
I FEEL BETTER.

15:02.333 --> 15:03.331
THAT'S GOOD.

15:03.333 --> 15:05.399
HOW BAD WAS IT?

15:05.401 --> 15:09.398
♪♪

15:09.400 --> 15:11.431
NOT BAD.

15:11.433 --> 15:14.365
DON'T LIE TO ME.

15:14.367 --> 15:17.965
WELL, HOW MUCH
DO YOU REMEMBER?

15:17.967 --> 15:21.298
I REMEMBER BEING COLD...

15:21.300 --> 15:24.332
AND THE NEIGHBOR --
THE PSYCHOLOGIST.

15:24.334 --> 15:26.398
YEAH.

15:26.400 --> 15:30.932
AND THEN I STARTED,
UM, SCREAMING.

15:30.934 --> 15:32.332
I DON'T KNOW THE REST.

15:32.334 --> 15:34.265
WELL, WHAT --
WHAT DID HE SAY TO YOU?

15:34.267 --> 15:36.398
HE CAME TO THE HOUSE.

15:36.400 --> 15:40.265
AND -- I DON'T KNOW.

15:40.267 --> 15:41.998
IT WAS WEIRD.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.431
HOW SO?

15:43.433 --> 15:45.432
I JUST DON'T WANT
TO TALK TO HIM AGAIN.

15:45.434 --> 15:46.732
-OKAY.
-EVER.

15:46.734 --> 15:49.665
OKAY.

15:49.667 --> 15:51.231
SO...

15:51.233 --> 15:55.032
NOW IS EVERYBODY GONNA BE
LOOKING AT ME LIKE I'M INSANE?

15:55.034 --> 15:57.031
NO. COME HERE.

15:57.033 --> 15:59.631
THESE PEOPLE SEEM
LIKE NICE PEOPLE.

15:59.633 --> 16:02.232
SO DID THE PEOPLE
IN OUR LAST BUILDING.

16:02.234 --> 16:03.632
♪♪

16:03.634 --> 16:05.098
THAT WAS DIFFERENT.

16:05.100 --> 16:06.865
I DON'T LIKE
BEING STARED AT.

16:06.867 --> 16:08.598
HON, I'M HERE. OKAY?

16:08.600 --> 16:10.898
YOU HAVE TO GO TO WORK.

16:10.900 --> 16:12.465
YEAH, BUT...

16:12.467 --> 16:14.998
AND I DON'T LIKE BEING ALONE
IN A NEW PLACE.

16:15.000 --> 16:17.465
OKAY. WELL, HOW 'BOUT WE
GET TO KNOW THE NEW NEIGHBORS?

16:17.467 --> 16:18.798
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK TO HIM.

16:18.800 --> 16:22.465
NO. N-NO. I MEAN...
ALEX ACROSS THE STREET.

16:22.467 --> 16:23.798
SHE SEEMS NICE.

16:23.800 --> 16:26.598
AND -- AND NATALIE
DOWN THE ROAD.

16:26.600 --> 16:28.665
THEY SEEM LIKE
REALLY NICE PEOPLE.

16:28.667 --> 16:30.332
NOT TODAY.

16:30.334 --> 16:32.265
OKAY.

16:32.267 --> 16:35.465
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WHEN I GO TO WORK, THEN?

16:35.467 --> 16:39.231
I THINK I'LL --
I WANT TO FINISH THAT BOOK.

16:39.233 --> 16:41.865
YEAH.
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

16:41.867 --> 16:43.332
-OKAY.
-OKAY.

16:43.334 --> 16:46.831
-AND I'LL MAKE YOU LUNCH.
-OKAY.

16:46.833 --> 16:49.032
PERFECT.

16:49.034 --> 16:50.432
I'M SORRY.

16:50.434 --> 16:52.365
TANYA.

16:52.367 --> 16:54.332
♪♪

16:54.334 --> 16:58.198
DON'T. OKAY?

16:58.200 --> 17:00.332
WHY DO YOU STAY WITH ME?

17:00.334 --> 17:02.465
♪♪

17:02.467 --> 17:04.465
LOOK AT ME.

17:04.467 --> 17:05.998
BECAUSE I LOVE YOU.

17:06.000 --> 17:07.465
I CAN'T GIVE YOU
ANYTHING.

17:07.467 --> 17:10.265
YOU GIVE ME
ALL THAT I NEED.

17:10.267 --> 17:13.065
IS THAT WHY YOU STOPPED
TAKING YOUR MEDS?

17:13.067 --> 17:14.532
CAN'T HAVE A BABY
IF I'M ON IT.

17:14.534 --> 17:16.798
BABE, WE --
WE DON'T NEED A BABY.

17:16.800 --> 17:18.932
-BUT I WANT ONE. I DO.
-OKAY.

17:18.934 --> 17:21.665
I KNOW YOU DO, BUT YOU CAN'T
STOP TAKING YOUR MEDS.

17:21.667 --> 17:25.132
I KNOW. I KNOW.
I KNOW.

17:25.134 --> 17:26.465
OKAY.

17:26.467 --> 17:28.799
BUT I WAS FINE UNTIL
HE STARTED TALKING TO ME.

17:28.801 --> 17:30.798
I WAS FINE. I HADN'T
TAKEN THEM FOR DAYS.

17:30.800 --> 17:33.198
I KNOW YOU<i> THOUGHT</i>
YOU WERE FINE.

17:33.200 --> 17:35.299
I WAS.

17:35.301 --> 17:38.032
LOOK. JUST DON'T
DO IT AGAIN, OKAY?

17:38.034 --> 17:40.632
LET'S JUST
GET SETTLED IN HERE,

17:40.634 --> 17:42.665
AND THEN WE CAN TALK
ABOUT ADOPTION

17:42.667 --> 17:44.865
OR MAYBE FINDING
A SURROGATE OR WE CAN --

17:44.867 --> 17:47.031
WE CAN'T AFFORD THAT.

17:47.033 --> 17:50.565
WE CAN WORK TOWARDS IT.
OKAY?

17:50.567 --> 17:52.032
I-I DON'T WANT TO TALK
ANYMORE ABOUT THIS.

17:52.034 --> 17:55.132
YOU ARE ALL THE FAMILY
THAT I NEED.

17:55.134 --> 17:57.798
I LOVE YOU.

17:57.800 --> 18:00.365
I REALLY LOVE YOU, OKAY?

18:00.367 --> 18:02.198
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

18:02.200 --> 18:05.531
OKAY.
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY.

18:05.533 --> 18:07.732
♪♪

18:07.734 --> 18:09.798
COME HERE.

18:09.800 --> 18:17.932
♪♪

18:21.100 --> 18:28.465
♪♪

18:28.467 --> 18:35.732
♪♪

18:35.734 --> 18:37.465
[ Line ringing ]

18:37.467 --> 18:39.532
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

18:41.867 --> 18:42.999
HELLO.

18:43.001 --> 18:44.931
HEY, I-I WAS JUST CALLING
TO CHECK ON YOU.

18:44.933 --> 18:46.399
Yeah, thanks.
I've been --

18:46.401 --> 18:50.532
I'VE BEEN HAVING A REALLY HARD
TIME SINCE LOSING THE BABY.

18:50.534 --> 18:52.865
I KNOW.
MARCIE, I'M SO SORRY.

18:52.867 --> 18:54.332
NO, IT'S OKAY.

18:54.334 --> 18:57.465
No, really.
Really I am.

18:57.467 --> 18:59.332
WELL, YOU KNOW,
I'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS BEFORE.

18:59.334 --> 19:02.565
AT LEAST I'M DIVORCED
THIS TIME.

19:02.567 --> 19:05.765
HEY.
CONGRATULATIONS, GIRL.

19:05.767 --> 19:07.465
THANK YOU.

19:07.467 --> 19:11.198
I WAS GONNA CALL AND, UM,
SEE HOW KELLY WAS DOING.

19:11.200 --> 19:14.265
MMM. WELL, SHE'S --
SHE'S BETTER.

19:14.267 --> 19:16.198
GOOD. GOOD.

19:16.200 --> 19:18.398
NO MAN IS WORTH
TAKING YOUR OWN LIFE.

19:18.400 --> 19:20.065
MNH-MNH. NO.
YOU CAN SAY THAT AGAIN.

19:20.067 --> 19:21.865
ESPECIALLY SOME
SORRY-ASS LOSER.

19:21.867 --> 19:24.065
YEAH, FOR SURE.

19:24.067 --> 19:27.932
YOU SHOULD FEEL REAL GOOD.
YOU GOT A GOOD ONE NOW.

19:27.934 --> 19:29.865
YEAH, I DO.

19:29.867 --> 19:33.399
AND I'LL KILL A BITCH
TO PROTECT HIM, TOO.

19:33.401 --> 19:37.065
THAT'S WHAT YOU SHOULD DO.

19:37.067 --> 19:40.598
YOU KNOW, MARCIE,
I-I REALLY AM SORRY.

19:40.600 --> 19:43.731
THANK YOU.

19:43.733 --> 19:46.765
HEY, LOOK, DID THE POLICE
TALK TO YOU?

19:46.767 --> 19:47.899
ABOUT?

19:47.901 --> 19:50.898
You know, what you did.

19:50.900 --> 19:52.965
NO.

19:52.967 --> 19:54.031
REALLY? I WONDER WHY.

19:54.033 --> 19:57.665
UM...
NO PROOF, I GUESS.

19:57.667 --> 19:59.198
AND IF THEY DO,
I'LL JUST --

19:59.200 --> 20:01.065
I'LL SEND 'EM
RIGHT OVER TO LARRY,

20:01.067 --> 20:02.998
AND HE CAN HANDLE THAT.

20:03.000 --> 20:04.932
[ DOOR OPENS ]

20:04.934 --> 20:09.065
OH, BUT, NATALIE,
A BEAUTIFUL MAN

20:09.067 --> 20:12.232
JUST WALKED THROUGH
MY DOOR WITH FLOWERS.

20:12.234 --> 20:15.865
UM, SO I'M GONNA
HAVE TO CALL YOU BACK.

20:15.867 --> 20:17.199
OH, A BEAUTIFUL MAN?

20:17.201 --> 20:19.132
Uh-huh. Brad.

20:19.134 --> 20:20.532
OH, OKAY.
I KNOW I GOT TO GO NOW.

20:20.534 --> 20:21.798
All right.
Talk to you later.

20:21.800 --> 20:23.665
ALL RIGHT. YEAH, I GOT TO GO
TO THE STORE ANYWAY.

20:23.667 --> 20:25.598
TALK TO YOU LATER.
BYE.

20:25.600 --> 20:27.599
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

20:27.601 --> 20:29.898
HI.

20:29.900 --> 20:31.665
HI.

20:31.667 --> 20:33.265
UH, WHAT'S THIS?

20:33.267 --> 20:35.998
I THOUGHT
I'D BRING YOU THESE.

20:36.000 --> 20:37.465
WHY?

20:37.467 --> 20:39.165
'CAUSE YOU
DESERVE THEM.

20:39.167 --> 20:42.232
OH.
WELL, THANK YOU.

20:42.234 --> 20:44.765
HOW MUCH WORK DO YOU
HAVE LEFT TO DO?

20:44.767 --> 20:47.965
OH, UM...
JUST A FEW MORE CALLS.

20:47.967 --> 20:49.698
CAN YOU MAKE THEM
FROM THE CAR?

20:49.700 --> 20:51.032
UH, YEAH. SURE.

20:51.034 --> 20:54.532
'CAUSE I'M ABOUT TO
TAKE YOU SOMEWHERE NICE.

20:54.534 --> 20:56.065
WHERE ARE WE GOIN'?

20:56.067 --> 20:58.565
IT'S A SURPRISE.
COME ON.

20:58.567 --> 21:00.665
-IT'S LIKE A DATE?
-YEAH.

21:00.667 --> 21:02.499
OUR FIRST OFFICIAL DATE.

21:02.501 --> 21:05.698
OHH. A GIRL
COULD GET USED TO THIS.

21:05.700 --> 21:07.998
I WANT YOU TO.

21:08.000 --> 21:10.865
LET ME GET MY PURSE.
I'M READY.

21:10.867 --> 21:17.932
♪♪

21:17.934 --> 21:24.865
♪♪

21:24.867 --> 21:31.732
♪♪

21:31.734 --> 21:35.531
HEY! HEY!

21:35.533 --> 21:36.665
HEY!

21:36.667 --> 21:38.532
AAH! WHAT?

21:38.534 --> 21:40.465
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?

21:40.467 --> 21:42.999
I'M MINDING MY OWN DAMN
BUSINESS. HOW 'BOUT YOU?

21:43.001 --> 21:44.999
YOU LOOKING INTO
THAT WOMAN'S HOUSE.

21:45.001 --> 21:46.599
HELL OUTTA MY FACE.

21:46.601 --> 21:48.732
RANDAL, I'M GONNA TELL THAT
WOMAN'S HUSBAND WHAT YOU DOIN'.

21:48.734 --> 21:51.999
AND I'M GONNA TELL HIM
THAT YOU GHETTO AS HELL.

21:52.001 --> 21:53.931
YOU REMEMBER
I CUT YOUR ASS BEFORE.

21:53.933 --> 21:55.332
OH, I REMEMBER.

21:55.334 --> 21:59.032
I DON'T EVER FORGET.
EVER.

21:59.034 --> 22:02.598
THAT WOMAN IS ALONE,
AND YOU KNOW SHE'S NOT WELL.

22:02.600 --> 22:04.065
<i> YOU'RE</i> NOT WELL.

22:04.067 --> 22:06.199
NO, NO, NO. YOU'RE THE ONE
THAT'S CRAZY AS HELL.

22:06.201 --> 22:09.265
YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT.
WELCOME TO MY WORLD, BABY.

22:09.267 --> 22:12.432
I WISH YOUR ASS WOULD'VE
BURNED UP IN THAT DAMN FIRE.

22:12.434 --> 22:14.365
♪♪

22:14.367 --> 22:15.998
OH, YOU KNOW WHO DID IT?

22:16.000 --> 22:18.265
♪♪

22:18.267 --> 22:21.599
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, YEAH. OH, I KNOW.

22:21.601 --> 22:22.898
WHO?

22:22.900 --> 22:24.731
IT WAS ME!

22:24.733 --> 22:26.632
-OKAY.
-[ CHUCKLES ]

22:26.634 --> 22:29.165
NO, THAT'S A -- THAT'S
A LITTLE TOO SMART FOR YOU.

22:29.167 --> 22:31.265
WELL, IT DON'T TAKE NOTHIN'
BUT CHEESE TO CATCH A RAT.

22:31.267 --> 22:34.032
WELL, A HOOD RAT LIKE YOURSELF
WOULD KNOW THAT.

22:34.034 --> 22:37.565
YOU BETTER LEAVE THAT WOMAN
ALONE. THAT'S ALL I KNOW.

22:37.567 --> 22:38.831
GET THE HELL
OUTTA HERE.

22:38.833 --> 22:40.099
GO ON AND GET BACK
IN THE HOUSE.

22:40.101 --> 22:42.132
-IT'S A FREE COUNTRY.
-GET IN THE HOUSE!

22:42.134 --> 22:43.798
OKAY.

22:43.800 --> 22:45.665
AND I'M GONNA TELL THAT WOMAN'S
HUSBAND WHAT YOU'RE DOING, TOO.

22:45.667 --> 22:46.798
-GO AND TELL HIM.
-I WILL.

22:46.800 --> 22:49.599
TELL HIM. BYE-BYE.

22:49.601 --> 22:51.665
AAH!
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:51.667 --> 22:54.465
THESE ARE NOT VERY
FLATTERING FOR YOU, BABY.

22:54.467 --> 23:00.465
♪♪

23:00.467 --> 23:02.798
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:02.800 --> 23:04.398
♪♪

23:04.400 --> 23:06.998
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

23:07.000 --> 23:09.532
ED?

23:09.534 --> 23:11.132
ED, I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

23:11.134 --> 23:14.265
-YOU ALREADY SAID THAT.
-OKAY, WHEN CAN WE TALK?

23:14.267 --> 23:16.465
SEE THAT THING THAT YOU'RE DOING
WITH YOUR MOUTH RIGHT NOW?

23:16.467 --> 23:17.765
IT'S CALLED TALKING.

23:17.767 --> 23:19.232
NOT HERE.

23:19.234 --> 23:20.665
WHY NOT HERE?

23:20.667 --> 23:22.865
BECAUSE I WANT US TO TALK
IN A PLACE THAT'S MORE CIVIL,

23:22.867 --> 23:24.565
WHERE IT'S JUST
YOU AND I.

23:24.567 --> 23:26.765
THE BEDROOM'S ALWAYS
WORKED OUT FOR US.

23:26.767 --> 23:29.565
YEAH, SO DID ME
SHOOTING OVER YOUR HEAD.

23:29.567 --> 23:30.832
AND YOU KICKED ME.

23:30.834 --> 23:33.565
YEAH, I DID.
LOVED IT.

23:33.567 --> 23:35.031
SO THE BEDROOM'S
OUT OF THE QUESTION,

23:35.033 --> 23:36.832
AND I WON'T LAY WITH YOU
IN THAT KITCHEN ANYMORE

23:36.834 --> 23:38.499
AFTER SURFER BOY AND YOU.

23:38.501 --> 23:40.965
LOOK, ED, I'M SORRY. I-I DON'T
WANT TO ARGUE WITH YOU.

23:40.967 --> 23:43.065
WELL, ARGUING AND TALKING,
IT'S THE SAME DAMN THING TO ME.

23:43.067 --> 23:47.731
CAN YOU FOCUS?
CAN YOU JUST PLEASE FOCUS?

23:47.733 --> 23:50.465
WITH THAT ASS, I CAN.
YEAH, SURE.

23:50.467 --> 23:52.798
CAN YOU MEET ME
FOR LUNCH?

23:52.800 --> 23:54.865
-YOU TRYING TO POISON ME?
-NO.

23:54.867 --> 23:56.332
WHAT ARE YOU
TRYING TO DO?

23:56.334 --> 23:58.198
SET ME UP SO HE KNOWS
WHERE I'M AT?

23:58.200 --> 24:00.065
WOW. SO YOU --
YOU'RE SCARED OF HIM?

24:00.067 --> 24:01.931
HAVE YOU EVER, EVER KNOWN
EDDIE TO BE SCARED?

24:01.933 --> 24:03.131
I AIN'T SCARED OF NOBODY.

24:03.133 --> 24:05.332
WELL, I MAY HAVE SOMETHING
THAT MAY SCARE YOU.

24:05.334 --> 24:06.865
I'VE SEEN
EVERY INCH OF YOU.

24:06.867 --> 24:09.465
THERE AIN'T NOTHING SCARY
UNLESS YOU'RE IN BETWEEN WAXES.

24:09.467 --> 24:11.331
GO AHEAD.
JUST KEEP DISRESPECTING ME.

24:11.333 --> 24:12.798
I'M -- I'M USED TO IT.

24:12.800 --> 24:14.199
I INTEND TO.

24:14.201 --> 24:16.299
I GET A BREAK IN TWO HOURS.
I'M GONNA TEXT YOU

24:16.301 --> 24:18.365
THE NAME OF THE RESTAURANT
WHERE YOU CAN MEET ME.

24:18.367 --> 24:21.899
JUST BE THERE.

24:21.901 --> 24:23.365
OKAY, MA'AM.
I'LL DO THAT.

24:23.367 --> 24:25.465
CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR THIS.
THIS SHOULD BE SO GOOD.

24:25.467 --> 24:28.465
YEAH, YOU'RE GONNA
WANT TO HEAR IT.

24:28.467 --> 24:35.798
♪♪

24:35.800 --> 24:43.132
♪♪

24:43.134 --> 24:50.665
♪♪

24:50.667 --> 24:53.265
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

24:53.267 --> 24:59.165
♪♪

24:59.167 --> 25:01.265
-HI.
-HI.

25:01.267 --> 25:02.765
MR. HOLMES,
HOW ARE YOU?

25:02.767 --> 25:04.498
UH, I'M GOOD, I'M GOOD.

25:04.500 --> 25:06.665
GOOD.
HOW'S YOUR WIFE?

25:06.667 --> 25:08.332
-SHE'S GOOD.
-GOOD.

25:08.334 --> 25:09.998
SHE SAID
YOU TALKED TO HER.

25:10.000 --> 25:13.532
-YEAH. YEAH, I DID.
-WHAT'D YOU TALK TO HER ABOUT?

25:13.534 --> 25:16.165
UH, YOU KNOW, JUST WELCOMED HER
TO THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

25:16.167 --> 25:17.965
YOU KNOW.

25:17.967 --> 25:21.098
-IS THAT IT?
-YEAH.

25:21.100 --> 25:22.632
YEAH.
WHAT'D SHE SAY?

25:22.634 --> 25:24.031
OKAY.

25:24.033 --> 25:26.032
WELL, YOU KNOW SHE'S GOT
A MENTAL ILLNESS, YEAH?

25:26.034 --> 25:28.632
YEAH. YEAH.
I-I PICKED UP ON THAT.

25:28.634 --> 25:29.965
DAMN SHAME.

25:29.967 --> 25:32.332
YEAH.
YEAH, IT IS.

25:34.967 --> 25:36.798
WELL, HERE'S THE THING.

25:36.800 --> 25:38.831
YOU KNOW WE'RE NEW
TO THE NEIGHBORHOOD, RIGHT?

25:38.833 --> 25:40.099
-YEAH.
-YEAH.

25:40.101 --> 25:43.099
WOULD YOU MIND DOING ME A FAVOR
AND NOT TALKING TO HER?

25:44.700 --> 25:47.432
THAT'S A -- THAT'S A LITTLE
RUDE, DON'T YOU THINK?

25:47.434 --> 25:50.598
YEAH.
BUT IT'S NECESSARY.

25:50.600 --> 25:54.265
♪♪

25:54.267 --> 25:56.532
-OKAY, SURE. SURE.
-THANK YOU.

25:56.534 --> 26:01.065
UH, OKAY.
I WON'T SAY ANYTHING TO HER.

26:01.067 --> 26:03.665
-THANK YOU.
-BUT...

26:03.667 --> 26:06.465
♪♪

26:06.467 --> 26:08.499
BUT WHAT?

26:08.501 --> 26:11.498
YOU KNOW SHE'S GONNA HAVE
ANOTHER BREAK, RIGHT?

26:11.500 --> 26:15.765
WELL, SHE JUST NEEDS
TO TAKE HER MEDS.

26:15.767 --> 26:17.765
WELL, WHAT IF SHE
DOESN'T TAKE THEM?

26:17.767 --> 26:19.965
I MEAN -- YOU KNOW, I WAS
THE ONE WHO HELPED HER OUT

26:19.967 --> 26:22.498
THE OTHER DAY, RIGHT?
YEAH, I UNDERSTAND THAT.

26:22.500 --> 26:24.198
AND -- AND LOOK.
I APPRECIATE IT.

26:24.200 --> 26:27.498
BUT JUST DON'T
TALK TO HER AGAIN.

26:27.500 --> 26:29.965
♪♪

26:29.967 --> 26:31.132
AH, I SEE.

26:31.134 --> 26:34.098
YOU'RE THE, UH --
YOU'RE THE JEALOUS KIND I SEE.

26:34.100 --> 26:37.732
HA. NO, SIR.

26:37.734 --> 26:40.532
I'M THE LOVING KIND.

26:40.534 --> 26:43.065
[ LAUGHS ]
WELL, ISN'T THAT CUTE!

26:43.067 --> 26:45.031
YOU HAVE A NICE DAY.

26:45.033 --> 26:47.365
YOU TOO.

26:47.367 --> 26:57.398
♪♪

26:57.400 --> 27:00.265
DON'T MESS WITH ME.

27:00.267 --> 27:03.332
I'LL MAKE THAT CRAZY BITCH
EVEN CRAZIER.

27:03.334 --> 27:08.932
♪♪

27:08.934 --> 27:14.332
♪♪

27:17.167 --> 27:23.832
♪♪

27:23.834 --> 27:26.265
-HI.
-HI.

27:26.267 --> 27:27.865
COME IN.

27:27.867 --> 27:29.532
THANK YOU.

27:29.534 --> 27:32.198
♪♪

27:32.200 --> 27:34.465
YOU LOOK GOOD.

27:34.467 --> 27:36.998
OKAY, RANDAL...

27:37.000 --> 27:38.865
♪♪

27:38.867 --> 27:40.998
[ SIGHS ]

27:41.000 --> 27:43.398
♪♪

27:43.400 --> 27:47.465
SORRY.
[ CHUCKLES ] WHAT?

27:47.467 --> 27:49.132
THIS IS ABOUT THE BABY.

27:49.134 --> 27:51.332
YEAH -- R.J.

27:51.334 --> 27:53.332
HIS NAME IS BRAD.

27:53.334 --> 27:55.332
NO. NO.
WE GOT TO TALK ABOUT THAT.

27:55.334 --> 27:57.265
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
THERE'S A FEW THINGS

27:57.267 --> 27:59.132
THAT WE NEED TO
TALK ABOUT, SO...

27:59.134 --> 28:01.932
YEAH. YEAH.
THERE ARE.

28:01.934 --> 28:03.798
HAVE YOU BEEN DRINKING?

28:03.800 --> 28:04.865
I-I HAD JUST ONE,

28:04.867 --> 28:07.198
YOU KNOW, JUST TO
KIND OF TAKE THE EDGE OFF.

28:07.200 --> 28:08.898
OKAY, WELL, LOOK.

28:08.900 --> 28:11.265
THAT'S GONNA HAVE TO BE
A DEAL BREAKER.

28:11.267 --> 28:14.332
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

28:14.334 --> 28:18.465
IF YOU'RE GOING TO COME OVER
HERE, YOU CANNOT DRINK.

28:18.467 --> 28:20.431
WAIT. WHO THE HELL YOU THINK
YOU'RE TALKING TO?

28:20.433 --> 28:22.499
[ SIGHS ] PLEASE JUST
DON'T GET UPSET.

28:22.501 --> 28:24.898
WE JUST NEED TO SET SOME
GROUND RULES WITH EACH OTHER.

28:24.900 --> 28:26.032
THAT'S IT.

28:26.034 --> 28:29.432
I'M JUST ASKING YOU TO
PLEASE NOT DRINK. OKAY?

28:29.434 --> 28:31.065
-LOOK, ALEX --
-OKAY?

28:33.400 --> 28:34.998
ALL RIGHT.

28:35.000 --> 28:37.132
ALL RIGHT.

28:37.134 --> 28:39.865
THANK YOU.

28:39.867 --> 28:41.199
SO WHERE IS HE?

28:41.201 --> 28:43.198
HE'S UPSTAIRS.

28:43.200 --> 28:45.865
OKAY.
WHAT, IN THE BEDROOM?

28:45.867 --> 28:48.065
-OKAY. RANDAL.
-WHAT?

28:48.067 --> 28:51.198
YOU ARE HERE TO SEE HIM,
AND THAT IS IT.

28:51.200 --> 28:53.765
OKAY. OKAY.

28:53.767 --> 28:55.432
OKAY.

28:55.434 --> 28:57.299
WAIT.
PLEASE WAIT.

28:57.301 --> 28:59.031
WAIT.

28:59.033 --> 29:00.732
WHAT?

29:02.567 --> 29:05.698
I NEED TO
TALK TO YOU FIRST.

29:05.700 --> 29:07.132
YOU ARE SO DAMN
CONFUSING TO ME.

29:07.134 --> 29:09.098
FIRST, YOU SAY THIS IS
ALL ABOUT THE KID.

29:09.100 --> 29:11.165
AND THEN NOW YOU SAY
YOU WANT TO TALK TO ME.

29:11.167 --> 29:14.265
WELL, THIS IS
ABOUT THE BABY.

29:14.267 --> 29:17.198
OKAY.
TALK, GIRL.

29:17.200 --> 29:20.265
-[ SIGHS ]
-WHAT?

29:20.267 --> 29:23.131
I-I THINK THERE WAS
A MIX-UP AT THE LAB,

29:23.133 --> 29:27.031
AND I WANT TO TAKE
ANOTHER DNA TEST.

29:27.033 --> 29:29.365
♪♪

29:29.367 --> 29:32.298
WAIT. WAIT. W-WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT? YOU...

29:32.300 --> 29:36.732
YOU SAID DR. RASTON
SWITCHED THE RESULTS.

29:36.734 --> 29:38.765
SHE DIDN'T.

29:38.767 --> 29:40.498
ALEX, I HEARD YOU.

29:40.500 --> 29:42.998
SHE DIDN'T DO IT.

29:43.000 --> 29:45.298
WAIT. SO THEN --

29:45.300 --> 29:48.532
THEN HOW DID IT COME BACK
AS NOT MY KID?

29:48.534 --> 29:50.332
♪♪

29:50.334 --> 29:52.665
I DON'T KNOW.
IT...

29:55.134 --> 29:57.198
DON'T PLAY WITH ME, ALEX.

29:57.200 --> 30:00.732
I'M JUST TELLING YOU.

30:00.734 --> 30:04.465
OKAY, SO -- SO W-WHAT
ARE YOU TRYING TO TELL ME?

30:04.467 --> 30:06.998
HUH? W-WHY DO YOU WANT ME
TO GET A DNA TEST?

30:07.000 --> 30:09.798
WAIT. WAIT. OH, YOU TRYING
TO TRICK ME? IS THAT IT?

30:09.800 --> 30:11.898
NO. GOD, NO!
NOT AT ALL!

30:11.900 --> 30:14.332
WERE YOU WITH
SOMEONE ELSE?

30:14.334 --> 30:15.798
OH, MY GOD.

30:15.800 --> 30:18.865
-HMM? LUSHION?
-NO!

30:18.867 --> 30:20.965
THEN WHY DO YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE ANOTHER TEST?!

30:20.967 --> 30:22.999
[ SIGHS ]

30:23.001 --> 30:25.332
-COME ON! TALK, GIRL!
-ALL RIGHT, LOOK.

30:25.334 --> 30:29.165
I WAS ONLINE, AND I WAS --
I WAS DOING SOME RESEARCH,

30:29.167 --> 30:33.398
AND -- AND THERE HAVE
BEEN CASES THAT --

30:33.400 --> 30:35.398
THE CHILD CAN COME OUT,
AND THERE'S, LIKE,

30:35.400 --> 30:37.665
A RECESSIVE GENE OR SOMETHING,
AND THEY LOOK LIKE THE --

30:37.667 --> 30:39.798
I DON'T KNOW -- LIKE THE
GREAT-GRANDPARENT OR SOMETHING,

30:39.800 --> 30:41.265
AND...

30:41.267 --> 30:43.398
[ SIGHS ]

30:43.400 --> 30:46.265
DO YOU HAVE BLACK
GREAT-GRANDPARENTS?

30:46.267 --> 30:48.732
-NO.
-DOES BRAD?

30:48.734 --> 30:50.532
NO. I-I DON'T KNOW.

30:50.534 --> 30:52.932
SO, THEN, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT, THEN?

30:52.934 --> 30:55.399
HUH?

30:55.401 --> 30:58.931
WE JUST NEED TO BE SURE.
RIGHT?

30:58.933 --> 31:01.999
♪♪

31:02.001 --> 31:06.065
NO. NO.
YOU WERE WITH SOMEONE ELSE.

31:06.067 --> 31:08.332
♪♪

31:08.334 --> 31:09.965
IS THAT WHAT
YOU'RE TELLING ME?

31:09.967 --> 31:13.232
-RANDAL, I WASN'T.
-ALEX...

31:13.234 --> 31:17.399
YOU TOLD ME THAT I WAS THE ONLY
BLACK MAN YOU'VE EVER BEEN WITH.

31:17.401 --> 31:21.599
NOW, IF THAT IS TRUE, THEN I
SHOULDN'T NEED TO TAKE A TEST.

31:21.601 --> 31:24.332
PLEASE JUST FORGET IT, OKAY?
NEVER MIND.

31:24.334 --> 31:27.832
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
NO, WAIT.

31:27.834 --> 31:31.798
SO THERE'S ANOTHER MAN.
HMM?

31:31.800 --> 31:34.065
RANDAL, DO YOU WANT
TO SEE THE BABY OR NOT?

31:34.067 --> 31:36.598
OH, YEAH. YEAH.
I WANT TO SEE THE BABY.

31:36.600 --> 31:39.265
MM-HMM. YEAH, I WANT TO GET
A REAL GOOD LOOK AT HIM.

31:39.267 --> 31:40.798
MM-HMM.

31:40.800 --> 31:42.865
SO WHO WAS IT?
WHO YOU WITH, HUH?

31:42.867 --> 31:44.598
COME ON.
GIVE ME THE LIST.

31:44.600 --> 31:46.532
OH, W-WHO --
WAS IT THE MAILMAN?

31:46.534 --> 31:48.865
IT WAS THE MAILMAN, WASN'T IT?
I KNEW IT.

31:48.867 --> 31:51.065
NOW YOU'RE JUST
BEING RIDICULOUS, OKAY?

31:51.067 --> 31:53.599
-PLEASE JUST DROP --
-ALL THAT TIME!

31:53.601 --> 31:55.132
SHH!

31:55.134 --> 31:56.465
YOU'RE HERE
AT THE HOUSE ALONE,

31:56.467 --> 31:58.398
AND YOU'RE GOING
TO THE P.T.A. MEETINGS

31:58.400 --> 32:01.065
AND ALL THE OTHER MEETINGS AND
TAKING THE KIDS TO THE LESSONS.

32:01.067 --> 32:03.132
ALL THAT TIME, YOU -- YOU
WEREN'T WITH ANYBODY ELSE?

32:03.134 --> 32:05.465
HUH? THERE WERE --
THERE WERE NO OTHER MEN?

32:05.467 --> 32:08.532
IS THAT WHAT -- IS THAT
WHAT YOU'RE TELLING ME?

32:08.534 --> 32:10.165
COME ON!
SPIT IT OUT, GIRL!

32:10.167 --> 32:12.298
YOU'RE COMPLETELY PARANOID.
YOU REALIZE THAT?

32:12.300 --> 32:14.265
OH. OKAY.

32:14.267 --> 32:16.065
LOOK, NEVER MIND.
ALL RIGHT?

32:16.067 --> 32:18.865
JUST NEVER MIND. FORGET IT.
FORGET I BROUGHT IT UP.

32:18.867 --> 32:22.532
PLEASE JUST -- PLEASE RELAX.
I DON'T WANT TO ARGUE WITH YOU.

32:22.534 --> 32:25.198
I'M STILL GONNA SUE
THAT DOCTOR.

32:25.200 --> 32:26.932
I'M STILL SUING HER.

32:26.934 --> 32:30.165
SHE DIDN'T DO IT,
RANDAL.

32:30.167 --> 32:35.198
THERE'S NO WAY THAT TEST SHOULD
HAVE COME BACK AS NOT MINE.

32:35.200 --> 32:37.165
THERE'S NO WAY.

32:37.167 --> 32:40.832
LISTEN, PLEASE.
YOU'RE IMPOSSIBLE RIGHT NOW.

32:40.834 --> 32:43.065
DON'T YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED?

32:43.067 --> 32:44.931
I ALREADY KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED.

32:44.933 --> 32:48.199
I KNOW GOOD AND DAMN WELL
THAT IT'S NOT BRAD'S BABY.

32:48.201 --> 32:50.865
I KNOW THAT.

32:50.867 --> 32:52.631
♪♪

32:52.633 --> 32:55.898
[ SIGHS ]
YES, WE KNOW THAT.

32:55.900 --> 32:57.899
YES. OKAY?

32:57.901 --> 33:01.898
♪♪

33:01.900 --> 33:07.132
JUST LET ME FIND OUT
THAT'S NOT MY BABY.

33:07.134 --> 33:09.265
YOU HEAR ME?

33:09.267 --> 33:10.532
DO YOU HEAR ME?

33:10.534 --> 33:12.932
YES, I HEAR YOU.

33:12.934 --> 33:16.065
JUST LET ME FIND OUT.

33:16.067 --> 33:17.865
DO YOU WANT
TO SEE HIM OR NOT?

33:17.867 --> 33:20.299
YOU THINK I DID
SOMETHING TO YOU BEFORE?

33:21.934 --> 33:23.598
YOU AIN'T SEEN...

33:23.600 --> 33:26.598
YOU LET ME FIND OUT
THAT'S NOT MY BABY.

33:26.600 --> 33:30.998
DO YOU WANT
TO SEE HIM OR NOT?

33:31.000 --> 33:34.065
OH, HELL, YEAH.
I WANT TO STUDY HIM.

33:34.067 --> 33:36.865
I WANT TO SEE HIS FACE.
I WANT TO SEE HIS EYES.

33:36.867 --> 33:41.431
WANT TO CHECK HIS NOSE,
HIS LIPS, HIS FEET,

33:41.433 --> 33:45.231
HIS HANDS, HIS FINGERS.

33:45.233 --> 33:47.099
FINE.

33:47.101 --> 33:52.431
♪♪

33:52.433 --> 33:57.432
♪♪

33:57.434 --> 34:00.398
LET'S GO.

34:00.400 --> 34:02.831
COME SEE YOUR SON.

34:02.833 --> 34:08.732
♪♪

34:08.734 --> 34:14.865
♪♪

34:14.867 --> 34:17.432
[ SOFT PIANO MUSIC PLAYING ]

34:17.434 --> 34:21.365
♪♪

34:21.367 --> 34:23.031
FANCY PLACE.

34:23.033 --> 34:26.099
YEAH.
THANKS FOR JOINING ME.

34:26.101 --> 34:30.265
LISTEN, I TOOK THE LIBERTY
OF ORDERING YOUR FAVORITE.

34:30.267 --> 34:32.332
-WAIT.
-WHAT?

34:32.334 --> 34:35.465
ARE YOU TELLING ME THAT
YOU'RE DYING OR SOMETHING?

34:35.467 --> 34:36.932
WHAT'S THIS ALL ABOUT?

34:36.934 --> 34:39.332
[ CHUCKLES ] NO. BUT I WISH YOU
WOULD TELL ME THAT YOU WERE.

34:39.334 --> 34:40.865
I'M SORRY, BABE.
CAN'T DO THAT FOR YOU.

34:40.867 --> 34:43.465
-DAMN IT.
-"DAMN IT" IS RIGHT.

34:43.467 --> 34:44.865
GOT A NICE LITTLE
POLICY ON YOU.

34:44.867 --> 34:48.198
YEAH.
I HAVE ONE ON YOU, TOO.

34:48.200 --> 34:49.832
THAT WHY YOU SENT YOUR
BOYFRIEND TO BEAT ME UP?

34:49.834 --> 34:51.098
OKAY, LISTEN.

34:51.100 --> 34:53.698
FIRST OF ALL,
HE'S NOT MY BOYFRIEND,

34:53.700 --> 34:54.932
THANKS TO YOU.

34:54.934 --> 34:58.398
AND AS I KNOW IT,
YOU STARTED EVERYTHING.

34:58.400 --> 35:01.065
NO. YOU OPENING YOUR LEGS
STARTS EVERYTHING.

35:01.067 --> 35:03.198
ALL RIGHT, LISTEN. I-I'M NOT
HERE TO ARGUE ABOUT THAT, OKAY?

35:03.200 --> 35:05.198
I DID NOT COME HERE
FOR THAT.

35:05.200 --> 35:08.165
WHAT ARE WE HERE FOR?

35:08.167 --> 35:11.698
ED. LISTEN.

35:11.700 --> 35:14.265
WE'VE BEEN DOING THIS
FOR WAY TOO LONG.

35:14.267 --> 35:16.398
I-I JUST WANT TO FIND A WAY
FOR US TO BE CIVIL

35:16.400 --> 35:20.165
AND A WAY FOR US TO COEXIST
FOR OUR DAUGHTER.

35:20.167 --> 35:22.299
TALKING ABOUT?
I<i> AM</i> CIVIL.

35:22.301 --> 35:24.298
ARE YOU -- ARE YOU
SERIOUS RIGHT NOW?

35:24.300 --> 35:26.765
YEAH, I'M SERIOUS.
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

35:26.767 --> 35:28.965
ED, YOU'RE THE MOST UNCIVILIZED
HUMAN BEING THAT I KNOW.

35:28.967 --> 35:30.365
BABY, THIS IS THE
CIVIL SIDE OF EDDIE.

35:30.367 --> 35:31.832
YOU KNOW THE OTHER SIDE.

35:31.834 --> 35:34.298
NO.

35:34.300 --> 35:37.732
ED, WHEN I MET YOU, YOU WERE
A COMPLETELY DIFFERENT PERSON.

35:37.734 --> 35:39.132
WAS I REALLY?

35:39.134 --> 35:41.265
YOU KNOW THAT YOU WERE.

35:41.267 --> 35:43.832
NO, BABY. THIS IS WHO
I'VE ALWAYS BEEN.

35:43.834 --> 35:45.498
NO, IT'S NOT.
YEAH, IT IS.

35:45.500 --> 35:48.132
I JUST PLAYED THE GOOD GUY
TO GET YOU TO FALL IN LOVE,

35:48.134 --> 35:49.598
BUT ONCE I HAD YOU...

35:49.600 --> 35:51.665
KIND OF CAME OUT OF THE CLOSET,
SO TO SPEAK.

35:51.667 --> 35:53.631
THIS IS WHO I'VE ALWAYS BEEN.
THIS IS ME.

35:53.633 --> 35:56.165
AH. ALL RIGHT.

35:56.167 --> 35:59.498
SO YOU WON'T EVEN CONSIDER
THIS CONVERSATION?

35:59.500 --> 36:00.798
YOU WON'T CONSIDER CHANGING,

36:00.800 --> 36:02.998
NOT EVEN FOR THE SAKE
OF OUR DAUGHTER?

36:03.000 --> 36:06.132
MIKA KNOWS HER DADDY VERY WELL.
DON'T YOU PULL HER INTO THIS.

36:06.134 --> 36:09.165
SO, WHAT, ED? YOU'RE JUST
GONNA CONTINUE TO DO DRUGS

36:09.167 --> 36:10.765
AND HARASS ME AND THREATEN
EVERYBODY THAT I DATE?

36:10.767 --> 36:12.232
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE
GONNA DO WITH YOUR LIFE?

36:12.234 --> 36:14.432
YEAH, YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT.
YOU KNOW THE SAYING.

36:14.434 --> 36:15.565
WHAT?

36:15.567 --> 36:18.265
IF I CAN'T HAVE YOU,
NO ONE'S GOING TO.

36:18.267 --> 36:21.332
ALL RIGHT.
WELL, I'VE TRIED.

36:21.334 --> 36:24.132
I GIVE UP. I'VE TRIED TALKING.
I'VE TRIED LEVELING WITH YOU.

36:24.134 --> 36:26.398
I'VE TRIED GIVING YOU
THE BENEFIT OF THE DOUBT.

36:26.400 --> 36:28.198
I'VE TRIED
EVERYTHING, SO...

36:28.200 --> 36:30.665
WHAT THE HELL'S THIS?
DIVORCE PAPERS?

36:30.667 --> 36:34.332
THESE ARE "SOLE CUSTODY
OF MY DAUGHTER" PAPERS.

36:34.334 --> 36:36.198
♪♪

36:36.200 --> 36:38.265
YOU BETTER GET THE HELL
OUT OF HERE WITH THIS.

36:38.267 --> 36:40.831
I WANT FULL CUSTODY.

36:40.833 --> 36:43.032
I DON'T WANT HER AROUND YOU
WITHOUT ADULT SUPERVISION.

36:43.034 --> 36:44.698
DON'T GIVE A DAMN
WHAT YOU WANT.

36:44.700 --> 36:47.565
I'M NOT SIGNING ANY OF THIS.
AND THIS...

36:47.567 --> 36:50.065
IS A LIST OF ALL THE SHIT
THAT YOU'VE DONE OVER THE YEARS

36:50.067 --> 36:51.932
THAT I KNOW ABOUT YOU.

36:51.934 --> 36:54.865
♪♪

36:54.867 --> 36:56.332
YOU'RE SERIOUS.

36:56.334 --> 36:58.965
I JUST WANT YOU
TO LEAVE ME ALONE.

36:58.967 --> 37:00.132
ED, STOP!

37:00.134 --> 37:03.365
YOU KNOW I WOULD<i> NEVER</i>
HURT OUR DAUGHTER.

37:03.367 --> 37:05.631
ED, WHEN I'M DONE
TALKING TO THIS JUDGE,

37:05.633 --> 37:07.898
NOTHING YOU SAY MATTERS --
NOTHING.

37:07.900 --> 37:10.365
OKAY. ALL RIGHT. SO STEVEN
PUT YOU UP TO THIS, HUH?

37:10.367 --> 37:11.699
-ARE YOU CRAZY?
-NO. ARE<i> YOU</i> CRAZY?

37:11.701 --> 37:13.832
YOU THINK YOU'RE WEARING
YOUR BIG-GIRL PANTIES TODAY?

37:13.834 --> 37:15.732
I KNOW I'M NOT PLAYING
WITH YOU.

37:15.734 --> 37:16.932
HEY, WAITER!

37:16.934 --> 37:19.132
CAN I GET A SIDE OF "GET
THIS BITCH OUT OF MY FACE"?

37:19.134 --> 37:20.299
CALL ME A BITCH
ONE MORE TIME.

37:20.301 --> 37:21.765
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU GO ON WITH THAT.

37:21.767 --> 37:23.432
I PUT UP WITH A LOT
OF BULLSHIT YESTERDAY.

37:23.434 --> 37:24.699
I'M NOT DOING THIS
FOR YOU TODAY.

37:24.701 --> 37:27.232
YEAH, I'M NOT DOING IT, EITHER.
I'VE TRIED EVERYTHING.

37:27.234 --> 37:29.432
YOU'VE TRIED TO COME IN HERE
AND THREATEN ME.

37:29.434 --> 37:31.265
-YEAH, THAT, TOO.
-LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.

37:31.267 --> 37:32.665
IF YOU PUT THIS
IN FRONT OF A JUDGE,

37:32.667 --> 37:34.265
I WILL HAVE HELL
RAIN DOWN ON YOUR LIFE.

37:34.267 --> 37:35.865
YOU HEAR ME?
YOU'LL NEVER SEE MIKA AGAIN.

37:35.867 --> 37:38.398
I'LL PUT YOUR ASS
IN A BOX.

37:38.400 --> 37:40.998
GET READY FOR IT, THEN.
'CAUSE I'M CALLING MY
LAWYER WHEN I LEAVE HERE.

37:41.000 --> 37:42.798
YOU WORK AT A 911 DISPATCH,
YOU BROKE BITCH.

37:42.800 --> 37:43.932
YOU CAN'T AFFORD A LAWYER.

37:43.934 --> 37:45.198
DID YOU JUST CALL ME
A BITCH AGAIN?

37:45.200 --> 37:46.531
YEAH, YOU'RE DAMN R--

37:46.533 --> 37:48.998
DO YOU NOT LEARN?

37:49.000 --> 37:50.699
ARE YOU DENSE
IN THE HEAD?

37:50.701 --> 37:52.765
YOU BETTER GET
YOURSELF PREPARED

37:52.767 --> 37:55.032
BECAUSE I'M CALLING MY LAWYER
WHEN I LEAVE HERE.

37:55.034 --> 37:57.365
-DO YOU UNDERSTAND THAT?
-YOU CAN'T AFFORD A LAWYER.

37:57.367 --> 38:01.132
OH, BABY, THAT'S WHERE YOU'RE
WRONG. LARRY'S MY LAWYER.

38:01.134 --> 38:02.899
SO YOU TWO REALLY WANT
TO DO THIS DANCE, HUH?

38:02.901 --> 38:04.232
YEAH, WE DO.

38:04.234 --> 38:06.332
AND FROM WHAT I HEAR,
HE'S REALLY GOOD AT IT.

38:06.334 --> 38:09.565
YOU BETTER GRAB YOUR STUFF
AND GET OUT OF MY FACE.

38:09.567 --> 38:10.765
NOW.

38:10.767 --> 38:12.498
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

38:12.500 --> 38:15.165
GLADLY.

38:15.167 --> 38:16.932
DAMN IT.

38:19.200 --> 38:21.831
I LEFT MY WALLET AT WORK.

38:21.833 --> 38:24.131
ED, YOU NEED
TO PAY THIS BILL.

38:24.133 --> 38:25.865
[ LAUGHS ] HEY, THIS GIRL
JUST ASKED ME TO PAY --

38:25.867 --> 38:27.165
ANYBODY WANT SOME FREE...?

38:27.167 --> 38:28.398
[ DINERS GASPING ]

38:28.400 --> 38:30.932
SHE'LL -- SHE'LL DO IT.
SHE'LL DO IT FOR A BURGER.

38:30.934 --> 38:33.065
ANYBODY? NO? YOU THINK
I'M PAYING THE BILL?

38:33.067 --> 38:34.699
YOU BETTER CALL
ONE OF YOUR BOY TOYS.

